Introduction

TNX (short for The New Six) is a South Korean boy group under P Nation. They were formed through the SBS survival show "Loud" and debuted on May 17, 2022, with the mini album "WAY UP."

Initially introduced as a seven-member group, TNX debuted with six members after Koki Tanaka withdrew before their official debut due to concerns over his age. The group quickly gained recognition for their versatility in singing, rapping, and dancing, with member Hwi contributing as a producer on some of their tracks.

Upon their debut, TNX revealed their official fandom name, THX, meaning "Together with TNX." In 2023, during their first anniversary celebration, they temporarily rebranded as The New Six before reverting to TNX later that year. On October 23, member Kyung Jun announced his military enlistment and subsequent departure from the group. P Nation later confirmed that TNX would continue as a five-member act.
